title: Afghan embassy officials summoned at GHQ in Rawalpindi
text:
Afghan embassy officials summoned at GHQ in Rawalpindi | 0 0 
RAWALPINDI: The Afghan embassy officials have been summoned at General Headquarters, read a statement from Inter Services Public Relations. 
According to the statement, a list 76 terrorists has been given to the officials at the Afghan embassy so that action is taken against them. However, the Pakistan army has demanded the terrorists be handed over to them if the Afghan government cannot take action. 0 0 Afghan embassy officials summoned at GHQ in Rawalpindi was posted in pakistan of Geo TV - https://www.geo.tv on February 17, 2017 and was last updated on February 17, 2017.
